    • Method Detail

      • invoke

        public JSValue invoke(JSObject instance,
                      java.lang.Object... args)
        Executes JavaScript function and returns result of execution as JSValue. This method blocks current thread execution until JavaScript function finishes its execution. If JavaScript function raises an exception, then JSFunctionException with error message that describes the reason of the exception will be thrown. Same error message will be printed in JavaScript Console. To get messages from JavaScript Console use ConsoleListener.
        Parameters:
        instance - JavaScript object the underlying function is invoked from. Pass null to invoke function as a global function.
        args - input arguments.
        Returns:
        result of JavaScript function execution. Never returns null.
        Throws:
        JSFunctionException - when exception occurs during function execution.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when instance is a valid JavaScript object, but it belongs to a different JavaScript execution context. The instance must be running in the same execution context as the current function.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when args parameters contain unsupported type.
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - when instance is already disposed or its JavaScript execution context isn't available anymore.

      • invokeAsync

        public java.util.concurrent.Future<JSValue> invokeAsync(JSObject instance,
                                                        java.lang.Object... args)
        Executes JavaScript function and returns result of execution as Future<JSValue>. This method doesn't blocks current thread execution and is invoked asynchronously changing result state depending on JavaScript function execution status. If JavaScript function raises an exception, then ExecutionException with error message that describes the reason of the exception will be thrown. Same error message will be printed in JavaScript Console. To get messages from JavaScript Console use ConsoleListener. If JavaScript function executes successfully, the result status will be set to "Done" and might be checked invoking the Future.isDone() method of the result instance. If JavaScript function execution has failed due to some reason, then the result status will be set to "Done" and might be checked invoking the Future.isDone() method of the result instance. In this case invoking the Future.get() method will throw the ExecutionException containing information about the failure.
        Parameters:
        instance - JavaScript object the underlying function is invoked from. Pass null to invoke function as a global function.
        args - input arguments.
        Returns:
        Future<JSValue> instance that might contain result of JavaScript function execution. Never returns null.
        Since:
        6.9

      • isFunction

        public boolean isFunction()
        Description copied from class: JSValue
        Indicates whether JavaScript value is a function. If this method returns true, then the value can be casted to JSFunction type. For example: 
         if (value.isFunction()) {
     JSFunction function = value.asFunction();
 }
        Overrides:
        isFunction in class JSValue
        Returns:
        true when JavaScript value is a function.

      • asFunction

        public JSFunction asFunction()
        Description copied from class: JSValue
        Casts the current JavaScript object to JSFunction type. If the current object doesn't represent a function, the IllegalStateException error is thrown.
        Overrides:
        asFunction in class JSValue
